Class Seller

java.lang.Object
User
Seller
public class Seller extends User
Template class (extends User) for Sellers. Stores elementary details about a Seller. Holds a list of Stores owned by the Seller in addition to the set of information in User.
instanceOf Seller is used to provide a Seller their customized permissions where required.

  • Constructor Details

    • Seller

      public Seller(String sellerString, boolean hasDetails, boolean hasStores)
      Parses a Seller object's String and converts it into a Seller object. Used while reading Seller(s) from memory. Inherently calls User(String userString, boolean hasDetails) to instantiate inherited fields to their values.

      Possible sellerString values dependent on memory:
      hasDetails == false => User.toString()
      hasDetails == true and hasStores == false => detailedToStringWithoutStores()
      hasDetails == true and hasStores == true => detailedToString()
      Parameters:
      sellerString - A Seller String
      hasDetails - Whether the Seller String is detailed (i.e. it contains blocked user, invisible user, and censored words)
      hasStores - Whether the Seller String is detailed and has stores (e.g. in Store object strings Seller(s) DO NOT contain stores)
      See Also:
      • User.toString()
      • detailedToStringWithoutStores()
      • detailedToString()

    • Seller

      email - The email of the seller
      password - The password of the seller
